We shall have to say more at 11 70 of this theory as applied to the universe of things: as here applied to this world of ours it is hardly perhaps consistent with what is said 556, that the process of destruction is much quicker than that of construction. Elsewhere too he argues at great length and with much earnestness that this world is of quite recent formation, and again that it not only can but must and will be destroyed in a moment of time.
